  "summary": "datetime-toolkit exfiltrates host and environment data on require",
  "details": "On load, index.js imports os, http, and https, then collects host identity and environment information (os.hostname(), process.env) and sends it over the network. The module is structured as a system-information exfiltration beacon rather than a date/time utility — the package name is decorative cover for a credential and host fingerprint stealer that fires when the module is required.",
